<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The INTER- prefix means "between" or "among" and is a bingo machine in Scrabble. At 5 letters, INTER- provides most of the tiles you need for the 50-point bonus — you only need 2 more tiles to complete a 7-letter bingo. With 300+ valid words, this prefix rewards players who hold common tiles together.</p>

<p>INTER- uses exclusively 1-point tiles, making it easy to accumulate on your rack without sacrificing scoring flexibility elsewhere.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why INTER- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

